values: i want to be famous. oh but not just any kind of famous. it's not that i'm picky...i don't care what kind of notoriety i receive. strangling things with pink shoelaces or making out with beautiful men like david letterman. pssh petty details... i just want to be famous enough to be able to appear on shows and shit with a fucking black eye and no one even comments on it. i don't have to politely acknowledge it with "i think i'm in love"(like amy sedaris ). no. it would be something that everyone would just accept. people (my fans) wouldn't try to imagine how i could have gotten it, they would instead just wonder what the other person looks like and shake their head, shed a tear and have a moment of silence for their family. yeah..i want to be that kind of famous.

yesterday was wonderful:::daisy makes the world shine brighter. ((wearing a flower in your hair doesn't hurt either)):::walked around the city. went to a  coffee shop on haight. talked about her intense romance over the barista's favorite tea. hit the ritzy vintage shops and the old school goodwill. went to amoeba. decided that the majority of my new musical acquisitions will be in vinyl form. drove back with the moon roof open. rediscovered the excitement of radio (you appreciate something a lot more when you don't have access to a skip or repeat button). went to the midnight movie, office space, with ben. chased it with la vic. caught up and gained some insight. we left in separate cars and at a stop light he blasted the yeah yeah yeahs. the light turned green and we drove alongside each other for the duration of maps and date with the night...it was grand . went home and watched looney tunes,  the nicest way to end a truly charming day.

Last night i went over to dan's apartment and we listened to my joni mitchell record and studied, we listened to more records and we made scarves out of this amazing multicolored blanket of his. it embodies fall. 

i've been thinking a lot about what fauzia said: one has to take responsibility for being misunderstood. and here i thought that it was everyone else's fault for not decoding my inarticulation. 

"couldn't figure out what made you so unhappy" elliot smith will be missed

*Bliss* I cry at the thought of it. Being happy. And it really is as fleeting as i feared.

It was my first day of the philosophy of religion class that i've wanted to get into for a week. i sat down. too embarrassed to wear my optic yellow "blondes have more fun" t-shirt, i swiftly pulled out my gray fuzzy sweater and successfully (i didn't bang my 'funny' bone on the table, or show my rolls off) put it on. I was really early and i had consciously brought along a book, tao of physics. the class started filling up and for the first time i wasn't concerned with who was coming in, i was just happy to be there. class is about to start and this tall slim guy with a mass poofy blond hair sits diagonal from me and leans over and flips the cover over just enough so that he could read the title. "Please don't tell me this is for a class". 

"No, actually, i wish."

He takes the book, flips through and points to a diagram of a wave and says "explain this to me." I was dumbfounded, i didn't know jack shit about physics, it was just interesting, the idea of it not reality. "Uh, i don't really know much about physics i just liked the correlation between it and eastern philosophy" Did you see that, did you the avid reader catch on? Sticking the word correlation in there to validate that i might be dumb enough to know what  basic concepts are, but that i am smart enough to have access to a thesaurus. 

i was walking with this girl after class and he followed us and before i said good-bye to her he interrupted with "Excuse me, but would you mind waiting outside the restroom while i urinate?" That's right, he said that. And you better believe i did.

We walked, we talked, i sat in on his physics 212 class, learned, had lunch and talked. but it wasn't a where are you from how many siblings do you have i want to "get to know you" conversation. it was a this is my take on things. we found beauty in spectacular objects overlooked by many, we loved communicating and meeting people (we were walking and this girl was looking at a map, stopped her and asked her if she needed any help finding anything and helped her talked to her for a bit, and i didn't even notice her at first). We met and it was Immediate and electric. He understood me. Not that he knew everything about me, but he understood that there was more than met the eye and that is all i can really ask for.

HE invited me to a party that night, we met up with this girl we had both at different times came up to and introduced ourselves to. she has the best style i've ever seen. eclectic, wild, beautiful, dangerous. Good times.

BUt here is where it counts. He invites me to dinner at his friend Dan's house. I think it's going to be this little low key apt. gathering. I walk into this huge house and andy moore is playing and there is a kitchen with a bar and just behind the bar is the nice looking blond standing behind her boyfriend as he cuts apples. To their left is a tall lanky guy with a scruffy beard and a striped red shirt frying something. he greets us he sets the appetizers, bacon and goat cheese and lays out crackers uniformly beside them. He begins to open this bottle of wine and his head is down, all his focus on uncorking it and he stands, slightly crooked, behind this fresh and erect, single sunflower that rests comfortably in this AMAZING glass bottle that was converted into a vase. I've never in my life wanted to take a picture so fucking bad. 

Anyway it is exhausting to replay all the magic of the night. We had an amazing dinner outside on the porch. The lighting was those string white xmas light wrapped around the banister and hanging from the roof. it was radiant. I felt like i was the audience in a movie. actually i'm not going to lie. i felt like i was with charlie and patrick from the perks of being a wallflower, and patrick was also embodied salinger's seymour (((and my deepest desire was to faintly resemble sam and franny))) we smoked up after and i can't even begin to repeat what dan had commented on. just brilliance and honesty like i've never witnessed before. jason, the guy i met, played three of the most perfect songs i've ever heard or seen performed. everyone took turns closing their eyes. we walked. we talked about the physics of walking vs. biking momentum and friction, it sounds bad  but it was great. we talked about beat poets and literature and me talk pretty one day, we exchanged non-fiction, hilarious, incredible anecdotes, we talked about the last time we'd cried. WE sat in jason's room and dan shared his thoughts and i cried. he offered to walk me home, i asked if i could walk him. we talked i admired i met his roommates who were great. at 2 am they played juanes and mana, two spanish artists and everyone sang in spanish and dan sat with his eyes closed absorbing. 

this was about jason and how much i am happy i've met him and how much of a force he will play throughout my life but it turned into a talk about dan. it turned into that because i've never encountered anyone who will make me cry at the thought of them. and i feel like sharing. ah I'll stop um more on jason later. i'm in love life at times, i hate anxiety i hate responsibility. school is background noise that sometimes creeps into my skin and taints the rest of my day. 

i don't know what to say. if we are god's creations i hope he invests a lot more into all of us, and enhancing it by sprinkling more moments like those and having people like you experience it too.

And then there was one... all my friends are gone now, off to college. I don't know where we will all be after a semester, who we will be, how we all have changed, if we're all still speaking (or picking up their phones and playing me "a reminder"). Unfortunately I'll be, relative to my current person, the same. There can't be much more of a difference,  i think anything from here will be more refined and unnoticeable. i'm tapped out of drastic transformations and deconstructions.

There really isn't anything better than a car full of great people listening to brilliant music, suspended from reality and silently being entertained by thoughts. 

I miss Kat a lot. I wanted to go the concert more than anything. no actually more than that I wish I got to say goodbye, say all the things I hadn't gotten a chance to. I miss the understanding. I have hurt her more than anyone that close to me and I don't know why.
I met up with brooks this week. my birthday was great. the day after paled, but at least I got to meet steve. this guy is so genuine and kind and perfect. 
I want to stay here, indefinitely. I hope these next few days drift along swiftly and smoothly. I will miss so much more than I could have imagined.

we all do something to get ready for the day. there is no truth. i'm still seeking if purity exist or if it's a raw form of ignorance. why am i typing? but while I'm at it... I hate it people talk as if they're in a movie, a very bad one at that. Everything is tainted. i am violent.I want so desperatly to love. I feel like it's an injustice I haven't been able to. The lackluster opportunties have arisendalsfk jl;asdk jfl'ai want to crash into a body into security into understanding mutal compassion the false idea of connection the uninhibited result. i am not fucking worthy not in a pity party kind of way if I am ever EVER lucky enough to have it I'll misuse it I'm still so young....the day will never come (don't want jinx it . i fall in "love" very easily and quickly one thing triggers attraction, i ignore all qualities that i despise and i emmerse myself in the hopeless painful unrequited bullshit and yearn for something I don't want knowingthat's exactly all i need. i am an appreciater, self proclaimed, self made and there is nothing worse than recognizing something good and not being able to create it for yourself. whether it's art, for obvious heritiary shortfalls, or communication. I don't have the gift of words and I fall so easily for someone who can use those devices effectively. To notbe understood. I am disabled. ifsssdflkjjlasdfkdjlakfjjlkadfsjj i am nothing I am boring i am ordinary nothing new nothing inspiring all of this, cliche riddled and all is sad because it's true. abyss. the silence in the exterior reality is beautiful when it matches up with the interior one. that is tao. what I can't stand is when the silence awakens and augments the insecurities the denied emotions the voices the memories the reality of me, what I've been hoarding and shoveling away into the subconscious. a petty frivolous existense keeps me afloat. idealism keeps my romatisicm fueled. one day i really will be watching the sky through a windshield while miles of landscape scrap by me, and I turn to brooks and he's happy enough to not say anything and not make me feel unwanted.

things at home are not well. I need to leave i can't wait. I love the connections I've made with everyone here but I need to be alone. I need to reconnect with relationships that time has made more significant than they really are (penn state). then I will be able to free myself from that as well. The one thing that has always driven my impulse and the cause of so much embarassment is my fear of not only the unknown, but possiblity (((sure! I'll go to that party there might be a chance I'll be missing out on something(one)))and this conditioned need to find a source of happiness outside of myself. 

"I want so badly to believe that there is truth, that love is real, and Iwant life and every word to the extent that it's absurd."

it's quite simple we want what we can't have cliche after cliche

i've never felt the cripling reality of unrequited love as much as I have in the last few days. to be continued. 

well, i'm off...who knows there might be chance something will happen...

Each man had only one genuine vocation--to find the way to himself. his task was to discover his own destiny--not an arbitrary one- and live it out wholly and resolutely within himself. Everything else was only a would be existence, an attempt at evasion, a flight back to the ideals of the masses, conformity and fear of one's own inwardness. I was an experiment on the part of Nature, a gamble within the unknown, perhaps for a new purpose perhaps for nothing and my only task was to allow this game on the part of primal depths to take its course, to feel its will within me and make it wholly mine. That or nothing!-- hermann hesses' demian--

I'm listening to the yeti mix cd. I have ashley to thank for introducing me to it. It being the store where I purchased this punk zine compilation known as "Despite Everything: A cometbus omnibus" that the store owner recommended (after I asked him to). So she indirectly opened me up to this beautiful indie man, err, store and I'm grateful, but I can only imagine where this fateful encounter can lead. 
I might be overheard talking about an obscure band I am currently listening to by a brooding jewish man . He will impulsively make the approach (very unlike him as he is very shy but was overwhelmed with the connection so much he even forgets who he is connected to). We'll soon realize we can't possible live without each other and so get married and live with our perpetually increasing vinyl collection. Ah good times. Thanks again ashely. 
It makes me think of the patterns of coincidences we can label either significant or natural. But only one perception can breed idealism and makes me happy, so I'll go with the latter.

Ashley was also the one that gave Kat this livejournal password. Thanks Kat.
